🔹 Problem: Valid Anagram

Given two strings s and t, return true if t is an anagram of s.

👉 Anagram = same characters with same frequency, order doesn’t matter
Example: "listen" and "silent" ✅

🧠 1. Brute Force Approach
💡 Idea:

For each character in s, try to find and remove it from t.

⏱ Complexity:
Time: O(n²)
Space: O(1) (if modifying string)
✅ Code (C++):
bool isAnagram(string s, string t) {
    if(s.size() != t.size()) return false;

    for(int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
        bool found = false;
        for(int j = 0; j < t.size(); j++) {
            if(s[i] == t[j]) {
                t[j] = '#'; // mark as used
                found = true;
                break;
            }
        }
        if(!found) return false;
    }
    return true;
}
📌 When to use:
Very small strings
No extra data structures allowed
Just to explain baseline in interview

⚡ 2. Better Approach (Sorting)
💡 Idea:

Sort both strings → if equal, they are anagrams.

⏱ Complexity:
Time: O(n log n)
Space: O(1) (ignoring sort space)
✅ Code:
bool isAnagram(string s, string t) {
    if(s.size() != t.size()) return false;

    sort(s.begin(), s.end());
    sort(t.begin(), t.end());

    return s == t;
}
📌 When to use:
Simple and clean
When modifying input is allowed
Good for interviews if you want quick correctness

🚀 3. Optimal Approach (Frequency Count / Hashing)
💡 Idea:

Count frequency of characters and compare.

✅ Approach A: Using Array (Best for lowercase letters)
⏱ Complexity:
Time: O(n)
Space: O(1) (fixed size 26)
bool isAnagram(string s, string t) {
    if(s.size() != t.size()) return false;

    vector<int> freq(26, 0);

    for(char c : s) freq[c - 'a']++;
    for(char c : t) freq[c - 'a']--;

    for(int count : freq) {
        if(count != 0) return false;
    }
    return true;
}
✅ Approach B: Using Hash Map (for Unicode / general case)
bool isAnagram(string s, string t) {
    if(s.size() != t.size()) return false;

    unordered_map<char, int> freq;

    for(char c : s) freq[c]++;
    for(char c : t) {
        if(freq[c] == 0) return false;
        freq[c]--;
    }

    return true;
}
